# Studio import path aliases

Physical folders (ADR-0038) are **not** import aliases in production source. MCP install targets use a **separate** `components.json` layer.

## Three-layer model

| Layer | SSOT | Purpose | Example |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **1 — Install** | `packages/shadcn-studio/components.json` | MCP/CLI **write** targets only | `components` → `@/components-quarantine` |
| **2 — Production** | `packages/shadcn-studio/tsconfig.paths.json` | TypeScript **read** in governed source | `@/components/ui/*` → `src/components-ui/*` |
| **3 — Vite runtime** | `apps/storybook/.storybook/main.ts` | Storybook resolve at dev/build | Must mirror layer 2 — no drift |

**Install command:** `pnpm studio:shadcn:quarantine` (overwrite OK in inbox) · **Production primitive add:** `pnpm studio:shadcn` (no overwrite on `components-ui/*`).

Gate: `pnpm check:studio-install-paths` validates layer 1 matches [`studio-import-path-policy.mjs`](../../scripts/governance/studio-import-path-policy.mjs).

## Layer 1 — components.json (install / quarantine)

```json
{
  "aliases": {
    "components": "@/components-quarantine",
    "ui": "@/components-quarantine/ui",
    "utils": "@/lib/utils",
    "lib": "@/lib",
    "hooks": "@/hooks"
  }
}
```

Physical disk: `src/components-quarantine/` (+ `components-quarantine/ui/` for primitives). **Not** exported from `@afenda/shadcn-studio` barrel.

## Layer 2 — tsconfig production map

| Import in source | Resolves to (disk) |
| --- | --- |
| `@/components/ui/*` | `src/components-ui/*` |
| `@/components/shadcn-studio/*` | `src/components-layouts/*` |
| `@/lib/utils` | `src/utils/utils.ts` |

**SSOT:** `packages/shadcn-studio/tsconfig.paths.json` — wire into all studio tsconfigs.

## Layer 3 — Vite runtime (Storybook)

`apps/storybook/.storybook/main.ts` `resolve.alias` must match layer 2. Symptom when drifted: studio typecheck passes, Storybook fails at runtime.

## Forbidden

- `@/components-ui/*` or `@/components-layouts/*` in studio/storybook source
- `@/components-quarantine/*` imports in production buckets (`components-ui/`, `components-layouts/`, `components-auth-shell/`) or ERP/Storybook consumers
- Physical-only aliases in tsconfig (without virtual counterparts)
- `apps/docs` / `apps/erp` importing studio internal aliases (use `@afenda/shadcn-studio` barrel or app-local UI)
- Pointing `components.json` install aliases at production paths (`@/components/ui`, `@/components/shadcn-studio`)

## Symptom → fix

| Symptom | Likely cause | First check |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Docs: `@/components-ui/button` not found | Docs `@/*` is local | `fumadocs-ui/components/ui/button` |
| Storybook fails, studio typecheck OK | Vite alias drift (layer 3) | `apps/storybook/.storybook/main.ts` vs SSOT |
| MCP overwrote production primitive | Install alias targets production | `pnpm check:studio-install-paths` |
| ERP imports quarantine block | Skipped promotion | `pnpm check:studio-quarantine-isolation` |
| Wrong component at runtime | Legacy `src/components/` tree | `pnpm check:studio-tsconfig-paths` |
| IDE red squiggle on `@/components/ui` | Main tsconfig missing virtual alias | `tsconfig.paths.json` wired into tsconfig.json |

## Gates

```bash
pnpm check:studio-install-paths
pnpm check:studio-quarantine-isolation
pnpm check:studio-tsconfig-paths
pnpm check:studio-import-zones
pnpm check:studio-paths   # tsconfig + import zones
```

